      • getAllBooks

        public static final java.util.List<Book> getAllBooks()
                                              throws java.sql.SQLException
        This method will be called when no search criteria has been entered in the UI and the user presses Search. It will get all books currently in the database and output them to the user since no filter criteria was specified.
        Returns:
        All books currently in the database.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - in case something goes wrong in the database while getting all the books.

      • createBook

        public final void createBook()
        When the user wants to create a new book, this method is called and will create a new book in the database. The new book's rowID will automatically be given by the database in order to avoid duplicate rowID's.

      • updateBook

        public final void updateBook()
        When a book's information needs to be updated, this method will be called and will set all the updated information to the each corresponding field in that book's rowID.

      • deleteBook

        public final void deleteBook()
        When a book needs to be deleted, this method will be called and will delete all the book's information from the database.

      • search

        public java.util.List<Book> search(SearchOption option)
                            throws java.sql.SQLException
        When a book needs to be searched for, this method will be called and filters the search criteria within the database to output the books that meet that specific criteria.
        Parameters:
        option - One of the four categories that can be searched for within the library.
        Returns:
        The list of filtered books for whatever was searched for.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - in case something goes wrong in the database while searching for a book.
